gw.api.diff.node.generator

Interface IKeyedNodeGenerator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractKeyedNodeGenerator, AddNodeGenerator, DiffTreeNodeGenerator, EntityNodeGenerator, RemoveNodeGenerator, TextNodeGenerator

    public interface IKeyedNodeGenerator
    Interface for classes capable of generating IDiffTreeNodes.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode getOrCreateNode(KeyableBean entity, java.util.Date effDate, java.util.Map<DiffTreeNodeKey,AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode> nodeMap)

    • Method Detail

      • getUniqueKey

        DiffTreeNodeKey getUniqueKey(KeyableBean entity,
                             java.util.Date effDate)
        Returns a unique DiffTreeNodeKey for the passed entity and effDate. For non-root generators, this key will include both the entity and the effective date as part of the key, whereas for the root generator, the key will consist of only the label.
        Parameters:
        entity - Entity for which to generate a unique key.
        effDate - The date to use as part of the key (can be null).
        Returns:
        A unique key for the passed entity.

      • getOrCreateNode

        AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode getOrCreateNode(KeyableBean entity,
                                            java.util.Date effDate,
                                            java.util.Map<DiffTreeNodeKey,AbstractOrderedDiffTreeNode> nodeMap)
        Returns the node from the given nodeMap by using a key created from the given entity and effDate. If no such node exists, inserts and returns a new node with the expected key.
        Parameters:
        entity - Entity for which to retrieve / create a node (used as part of key creation).
        effDate - Date for which to retrieve / create a node (used as part of key creation).
        nodeMap - Map of nodes.
        Returns:
        An existing or newly created node for the passed entity.
        See Also:
        getUniqueKey(KeyableBean, Date)
